HEADWORD: Trullization
<hw>Trul`li*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trullissatio</ets>, from <ets>trullissare</ets> to trowel, to
plaster, fr. <ets>trulla</ets> a trowel.]</ety> <def>The act of laying
on coats of plaster with a trowel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truly</ent>⟦br⟧
